* {{ja-r|薬|くすり}}: a medicine or drug {{qualifier|see below}}
* {{ja-r|薬%子|くす%こ}}: an [[unmarried]] [[young woman]] serving at the [[imperial]] [[court]] who tastes the ceremonial [[spiced]] [[sake]] at [[New Years]]
* {{ja-r|薬%師|くす%し}}: a [[doctor]] {{qualifier|archaic}}
* {{ja-r|薬%師%指|くす%し%ゆび}}: archaic alternate for {{ja-r|薬%指|くすり%ゆび}}: the [[ring finger]]
* {{ja-r|薬%玉|くす%だま}}: an [[ornamental]] [[scented]] [[ball]] made of flowers or other [[aromatic]]s, displayed in early May
* {{ja-r|薬%殿|くす%どの}}: during the [[w:Heian period|Heian period]], the [[consultation]] [[office]] of the [[court]] [[physician]]
* {{ja-r|薬%練|くす%ね|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|薬%煉|くす%ね|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|天%鼠%矢|く%す%ね}}: [[pine]] [[sap]] boiled in [[oil]] to make a strong [[resin]] used to [[reinforce]] [[bowstring]]s and other things
* {{ja-r|薬%練%糸|くす%ね%いと|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|薬%煉%糸|くす%ね%いと}}: a [[string]] with ''kusune'' applied to it
* {{ja-r|樟|くすのき}}, {{ja-r|楠|くすのき}}: the [[camphor]] [[tree]]
